arts.sum: Their record of having only conceded one goal in their last six games meant a difficult task for Stoke, particularly when referee Will Finnie bizarrely missed a clear penalty and red card when Wouter Burger was tugged back by Jake Cooper in the six-yard box at the start of the second half. arts.ttl: Stoke City vs Millwall live - Team news from early kick-off at bet365 Stadium - Stoke-on-Trent Live
arts.sum: Stoke City welcome in-form Millwall to the bet365 Stadium in the final match of a busy period heading into another international break. Stoke have crammed in the games since the last fortnight off for internationals and this is the seventh in three weeks, having won the last two against Derby County and Blackburn Rovers.
